Yes and no. The fastest way to get to the base is to run through it, as one can do at first base, provided you run straight through and don't take the turn towards 2nd. But at all other bases, you need to slow down to stay at the base; if you run past it, you can be tagged out.
So, at 2d, 3d, and home, sliding may not be faster in arrival to the base but the extra distance that the fielder has to reach down to tag the runner sliding by more than makes up for the loss of speed vs. the straight run to but not /through/ the base.

